aas:election_record.label: Maine 1825 U.S. Congress, 3rd District

aas:ballot.aas:note: The first ballot for this office occured in 1824.

aas:sub_unit.name: Dresden
aas:sub_unit.aas:note: The Maine Gazette, 7 January 1825, reported 20 votes for Ebenezer Herrick and 8 votes for Ebenezer Thatcher.

aas:sub_unit.name: Woolwich
aas:sub_unit.aas:note: The Maine Gazette, 7 January 1825, reported 3 votes for Ebenezer Herrick, 13 votes for Albert Smith, and 16 votes for EbenezerThatcher.

aas:election_record.aas:reference: The Independant Statesman and Maine Republican (Portland). March 25, 1825
Eastern Argus (Portland). March 7, 1825 + American Advocate (Hallowell). March 12, 1825
Dubin, Michael J. United States Congressional Elections, 1788-1997. Jefferson, N.C.: McFarland and Company, 1998
